5 Ways to Start Getting Clients After Your Makeup Course

1. Local Ads Still Work
Print some affordable flyers and distribute them in salons, boutiques, and beauty parlours near you.

2. Start a Social Media Portfolio
Post 3–4 makeup looks every week (even on friends or self) with before-after pics. Show results.

3. Free/Demo Looks to Build Trust
Do 3–5 free looks for close friends or family and ask them to post and tag you. This builds credibility and reach.

4. WhatsApp Status = Secret Weapon
Post your makeup reels, transformations, and offers on WhatsApp Status daily. You’ll get clients from your own contacts.

5. Collaborate Locally
Partner with photographers, boutiques, or salons. They refer brides; you refer clients back. Win-win!
